Delta State police command has arrested the Proprietor of Grace Life International School in Oghara-Efe, Ethiope East local government area of the state, Mr. Michael Anigholor for allegedly raping a corps member posted to his school for her primary assignment. The state commissioner of police, Mr Hafiz Mohammed Inuwa, who briefed journalists yesterday in Asaba, disclosed that the corps member reported at the school for her primary assignment and after her documentation, the suspect who is the proprietor of the school  took her to his house in Sapele and had carnal knowledge of her without her consent. He added that the suspect has been charged to court. CP Inuwa further stated that two fake Naval officers, Owen Louis 22 and Yusuf Rasheed 26, were arrested in Warri while they were beating a fashion designer. CP said that following a quarrel between a tailoring apprentice attached to Jashet Aluma Fashion outfit, that the two fake officers were hired to beat up his boss who is the owner of the outfit and in the process, they were arrested by police patrol team attached to Warri Area command. “Having received brief on the crime situation on my assumption of duty as Delta State commissioner of police, the command’s security architecture was reviewed with a view to repositioning its operations for optimal performance”. “Between January 2nd this year and now, no fewer than 41 armed robbers, 8 kidnapping suspects, 16 cultists were arrested and 266 live expended cartridges were recovered.” The Police Commissioner noted that efforts are being made to ensure that criminally minded herdsmen are chased out of the state, adding that the command will collaborate with all the stakeholders in the state to ensure that crime is reduced to the barest minimum.    